public class ClassMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements Serializable

Maps from classes to objects (not necessarily objects of that class). Attempts to adhere to the Liskov Substitution principle in that requests for a class that does not have any value associated with it will retrieve the value for its nearest superclass.
